					</div>
				<h1 itemprop="headline" class="entry-title">Today in Small Business: Independent Contractors</h1>
		<div class="story-meta-footer">
			<address class="byline author vcard" itemprop="author creator" itemtype="//schema.org/Person">
				By Gene Marks			</address>
			<!-- date published --><time class="dateline " datetime="2014-08-28T17:13:14+00:00" itemprop="datePublished">August 28, 2014 1:13 pm</time>
			<!-- date updated --><span class="visually-hidden updated">August 28, 2014 1:13 pm</span><button class="button comments-button  theme-kicker" data-skip-to-para-id="">
</button>
		</div>
			</header>
		<div class="entry-content"><div id="sharetools-story" class="sharetools theme-classic sharetools-story" data-shares="email|Email,facebook|Share,twitter|Tweet,save|Save,show-all|More,ad" data-url="//boss.blogs.nytimes.com/2014/08/28/today-in-small-business-independent-contractors/" data-title="Today in Small Business: Independent Contractors" data-description="Thanks to protesting workers, the president of a family supermarket gets his job back. Section 179 deductions are changing. Do you recline in your airline seat?">
				<div class="ad sharetools-inline-article-ad"></div>
				<div id="MiddleLeft" class="ad middle-left-ad nocontent robots-nocontent"></div>
				</div><div class="inlineModule"><div class="entry"><h6 class="kicker"><a href="//boss.blogs.nytimes.com/category/dashboard/">Dashboard</a></h6><p class="summary">A daily roundup of small-business developments.</p></div></div>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">Whatâs affecting me, my clients and other small-business owners today.</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><strong>The Economy</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Consumers <a href="//blogs.wsj.com/economics/2014/08/27/consumers-have-confidence-but-not-lots-of-cash/?">have confidence</a> but not a lot of cash.</li>
<li>The Congressional Budget Office now predicts that the economy <a href="//www.csmonitor.com/Business/Latest-News-Wires/2014/0827/CBO-US-economy-to-grow-by-1.5-percent-in-2014">will grow</a> by 1.5 percent in 2014.</li>
<li><a href="//www.insurancejournal.com/news/national/2014/08/27/338715.htm">Home construction</a> jumped 15.7 percent in July.</li>
<li>Small businesses with one to 10 employees experienced <a href="//www.accountingtoday.com/news/payroll/surepayroll-sees-increase-in-small-business-hiring-in-august-71751-1.html">a month-over-month increase in hiring</a> of one-tenth of a percent this month, according toÂ SurePayroll.</li>
</ul>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><strong>Taxes</strong></p>
<ul>
<li><a href="//www.washingtonpost.com/business/on-small-business/small-business-big-mistake-classifying-employees-as-independent-contractors/2014/08/27/d2af22bc-2d40-11e4-994d-202962a9150c_story.html">Classifying employees</a> as independent contractors cost one small employer thousands in back taxes.</li>
<li>Here are five <a href="//www.businessnewsdaily.com/7032-small-business-tax-issues.html">tax changes</a> &#8212; including one to Section 179 deductions &#8212; that business owners should expect.</li>
</ul>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><strong>Employees</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Thanks to <a href="//www.nytimes.com/2014/08/28/us/market-basket-settlement.html">protesting workers</a>, the president of a family supermarket gets his job back.</li>
</ul>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"> <span id="more-88201"></span><br />
<strong>Management</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>General Motors is <a href="//www.mbtmag.com/news/2014/08/gm-move-cadillac-srx-production-tenn">moving production</a> from Mexico to Tennessee.</li>
<li>The cupcake store Crumbs may be <a href="//online.wsj.com/articles/crumbs-bake-shop-to-reopen-stores-after-court-approval-1409078024">back in business</a>.</li>
</ul>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><strong>Start-Up</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>As their product goes on sale, two inventors talk about <a href="//www.nytimes.com/2014/08/28/garden/the-dirt-on-your-sponge.html">how they came up with the SpongeBath</a>.</li>
<li>In a video, a business owner talks about the <a href="//mashable.com/2014/08/27/small-business-build-out/#:eyJzIjoidCIsImkiOiJfMXJhbHZlMTNsaW9pcnozemZqeWdoYWcxMW5fIn0">nanobrewery he is about to open</a> in Detroit.</li>
</ul>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><strong>Health Care</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Mississippiâs small-business health insurance exchange is <a href="//djournal.com/news/small-business-exchange-spurs-interest/">up and spurring interest</a> among small-business owners.</li>
<li>A little-known <a href="//www.vox.com/2014/8/27/6074219/obamacare-has-a-ceo-tax-and-it-just-raised-72-million">Affordable Care Act tax</a> on health insurance executives&#8217; salaries raised $72 million in revenue last year.</li>
</ul>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><strong>Retailing</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>A retailing consultant warns that restaurant operators <a href="//nrn.com/hr-training/restaurant-operators-must-plan-minimum-wage-hikes-other-costs?page=1">must plan</a> for minimum wage increases.</li>
<li>Teenagers are <a href="//www.nytimes.com/2014/08/28/business/less-prep-more-plugs-teenagers-favor-tech-over-clothes.html">choosing tech over clothes</a>.</li>
<li>Nordstrom is making it easier for customers to <a href="//chainstoreage.com/article/nordstrom-makes-instagram-shoppable-launches-like2buy-platform">shop on Instagram</a>.</li>
</ul>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><strong>Finance</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>A writer offers <a href="//www.forbes.com/sites/tykiisel/2014/08/26/two-reasons-to-be-sweet-on-maria-contreras-sweet/">two reason to be pleased</a> with the Small Business Administrationâs Maria Contreras-Sweet.</li>
<li>Jessica Alba&#8217;s company <a href="//www.entrepreneur.com/article/236906">raises $70 million</a> as it prepares to go public.</li>
</ul>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><strong>Marketing</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>According to <a href="//www.cnbc.com/id/101949001">this survey</a>, millennials prefer plastic.</li>
</ul>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><strong>Sales</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Here is a list of basic tips to <a href="//www.inc.com/aj-agrawal/how-to-land-your-next-big-client.html">close sales</a>.</li>
<li>And here is why the <a href="//www.theglobeandmail.com/report-on-business/small-business/sb-marketing/sales/negotiating-price-doesnt-have-to-be-part-of-the-sales-process/article20187604/">best sales representatives</a> don&#8217;t negotiate.</li>
</ul>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><strong>Business Travel</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>The <a href="//www.nytimes.com/2014/08/28/upshot/dont-want-me-to-recline-my-airline-seat-you-can-pay-me.html?abt=0002&amp;abg=1">case for reclining</a> in an airline seat.</li>
</ul>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><strong>Social Media</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Twitter&#8217;s <a href="//www.pocket-lint.com/news/130549-want-to-see-who-reads-your-tweets-twitter-s-analytics-dashboard-reveals-all">analytics dashboard</a> is now available to see whoâs reading your tweets.</li>
<li>A food blogger <a href="//www.entrepreneur.com/article/236896">who persuaded</a> Chick-fil-A and Subway to make menu changes is taking on Starbucksâ Pumpkin Spice Latte.</li>
</ul>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><strong>Around the Country</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Meet a New Yorker who makes <a href="//www.slate.com/blogs/business_insider/2014/08/27/anthony_green_tutors_rich_kids_via_skype_through_his_company_test_prep_authority.html">$1,000 an hour</a> offering SAT-prep tutoring on Skype.</li>
<li>The Philadelphia Police Department is asking more small businesses to participate in its <a href="//www.newsworks.org/index.php/local/item/72010-citing-270-arrests-philly-officials-pushing-to-expand-safecam-surveillance-program/">security camera sharing</a> program.</li>
<li>Local officials near Portland, Ore., have approved a tax break for Intel Corporation that <a href="//www.foxbusiness.com/markets/2014/08/27/intel-to-get-local-tax-breaks-worth-about-2-billion-on-equipment-tools-in/">could be worth</a> about $2 billion.</li>
<li>Here are 20 cities <a href="//www.vox.com/xpress/2014/8/27/6074213/lowest-unemployment-rate-cities">with less than 4 percent unemployment</a>.</li>
</ul>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><strong>Around the World</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Google <a href="//venturebeat.com/2014/08/27/google-wants-to-nurture-korean-startups-opens-campus-location-in-seoul/"> opens a campus in Seoul</a> to nurture Korean start-ups.</li>
<li>Small-business owners in Vancouver <a href="//www.columbian.com/news/2014/aug/26/small-business-owners-vancouver-voice-opposition-o/">voice opposition</a> to building an oil-by-rail terminal.</li>
<li>A Melbourne cafe <a href="//www.theguardian.com/lifeandstyle/2014/aug/27/melbournes-cat-cafe-like-aa-only-for-cat-owners">caters to cat owners</a>.</li>
</ul>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><strong>Washington</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Medicare is <a href="//www.nytimes.com/2014/08/28/upshot/medicare-not-such-a-budget-buster-anymore.html?abt=0002&amp;abg=1">not such a budget-buster</a> anymore.</li>
</ul>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><strong>Technology</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>JPMorgan Chase and other banks are struck by <a href="//www.nytimes.com/2014/08/28/technology/hackers-target-banks-including-jpmorgan.html?">a coordinated cyberattack</a>.</li>
<li>The Pandora music service <a href="//www.cnet.com/news/pandoras-google-glass-app-puts-music-right-into-your-bones/#f">creates an app</a> for Google Glass.</li>
</ul>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><em>Gene Marks owns the <a href="//www.marksgroup.net">Marks Group</a>, a Bala Cynwyd, Pa., consulting firm that helps clients with customer relationship management. You can follow him on <a href="https://www.twitter.com/genemarks">Twitter</a>.</em></p>
